author: @carmelradaza
text:
One thing I love about how SM manages aespa is that early on in their career they are given room to learn and grow as young artists. That chance to try their own ideas. It's not much but it helps them showcase their grow.

The first tour was really more of a learning process for aespa. It was perfectly structured that they only needed to perform what they learned. A perfect starting point per se.

Now, this second tour, this was more of aespa's applying what they learned on the first tour and the things they want to try and do. This setlist felt less structured and shows more of their personalities. They look really like clueless elementary students on the first tour practice video. But now they look like college students with enough background knowledge that they could actively share their ideas knowing what works and not.
